/*S*/ Einleitung
/*S*/ Einleitung-Node
@node "Introduction" "FreshIconizer - Introduction"
@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}@{u}1. Einleitung@{uu}@{ub}@{FG TEXT}
@{i}To  avoid  useless  reading  this  documentation,  it  is  mentioned   that
FreshIconizer   runs  only  on  AMIGA-Computers  with  OS  2.0  or  better.
FreshIconizer is a program, which uses the Intuition-Add-On @{"MUI" LINK "mui.copyright"}  by  Stefan
Stuntz. So MUI (at least version 3.x is required.)@{ui}

@{"Disclaimer" LINK "disclaim"}
@{"Lawful" LINK "copyright"}

@{b}What is FreshIconizer?@{ub}

FreshIconizer is a program, which shall make it easier to install or update
FreshIcons.

Of course, it's possible to tell FreshIconizer which informations  hold  in
the icons you want to take over.

If you want to give a dataobject a new icon, so drop the  new  one  over  a
source-box   and   drop   the  dataobject  you  want  to  change  into  the
destination-box. The destination-object gets its new icon immediately.

Last change of FreshIconizer: July, 31th 1996

FreshIconizer V1.21 was compiled with SAS/C V6.56.  FreshIconizer  supports
the locale.library but has no ARexx-port.
@endnode
/*E*/
